#import "../../knot-typst-package/lib.typ": *
#show: codly-init

= Test Graphics Options

This example demonstrates the new graphics options parsing (Phase 4 preparation).

== Test 1: Default graphics settings

This chunk will use the hardcoded defaults:
- fig-width: 7 inches
- fig-height: 5 inches
- dpi: 300
- format: svg

```{r plot1}
#| eval: false
#| echo: true
#| output: false
# Defaults will be: 7x5 inches, 300 dpi, svg
x <- 1:10
y <- x^2
plot(x, y, main = "Default size plot")
```

== Test 2: Custom chunk-level options

This chunk overrides all graphics settings:

```{r plot2}
#| eval: false
#| echo: true
#| output: false
#| fig-width: 10
#| fig-height: 8
#| dpi: 600
#| fig-format: png
#| fig-alt: "A large high-resolution scatter plot"
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(iris, aes(Sepal.Length, Sepal.Width, color = Species)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14)
```

== Test 3: Partial overrides

This chunk only overrides width and dpi:

```{r plot3}
#| eval: false
#| echo: true
#| fig-width: 5
#| dpi: 150
# height: 5 (default), format: svg (default)
hist(rnorm(1000), main = "Small plot, lower DPI")
```

== Notes

Graphics rendering is not yet implemented (Phase 4).
These options are parsed and will be used when we implement:
- R device creation (svg/png/pdf)
- ggsave() integration
- Image export to `_knot_files/`
